RACE.RACE_TEXT: PERCY WARNER RACE 1 2 3/4M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 35000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 120 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including a pprentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JIMMY P was well placed early never far back holding second then third position, drew clear when asked by three lengths before the last fence and increased the margin handily in the stretch. WICKED WEST (IRE) settled to the back of the field, made a move with two hurdles remaining and closed with a rush. FIGHTINIRISHTABIT was away alertly, set the early pace well ahead of the rest, jumped well, was challenged mid race by GO POKE THE BEAR, and weakened at the last fence. GO POKE THE BEAR settled back of the field early, dueled for the lead the second mile, but came up empty. PING PONG CHAMP settled midpack, went wide before the last to make space, rider asked but there was no response. ZIGGLE POPS (GB) settled in the back early, traveled on an inside path and was never a threat. SEIZING THE DREAM ran in the back of the field first 1 1/2 miles, made a bid at the second to last, then flattened. CAPTAIN MIDDLETON (IRE) ran midpack, made a bid before the last, then weakened. ANIMAL KINGSTON ran midpack, failed to respond and faded before the last. SOLOMOON (GB) ran midpack, tired and pulled up before the last. HOOROO (IRE) kept with the pace early, settled midrace, then tired and pulled up before the last.
